We use nested loops to iterate through all possible substrings of the string s. For each substring, we check if the characters at the current position are the same. If they are, we increment the count by the number of characters in the substring (n - i - j + 1), where n is the length of the string, i is the starting index, and j and k are the ending indices of the substring. This approach has a time complexity of O(n^3) and a space complexity of O(1), which is efficient for this problem.

